Notice No:  01-193

June 7, 2001


To:

All NYMEX Division Members


From:

Donna Talamo, Director

Office of the Corporate Secretary


Re:

NYMEX BOARD EXTENDS PROPRIETARY FEE REDUCTION PROGRAM


At its meeting on June 6, 2001, the NYMEX Board of Directors determined to

extend the current Proprietary Fee Reduction Program (&Program8) through

July 31, 2001.


Pursuant to the Program, Member Firms and individuals members who own seats

will have their NYMEX Division fees reduced by 12 cents per round turn (6

cents per trade side).


Individual members who lease their seats, or hold a membership under an ABC

Agreement, will have their NYMEX Division fees reduced by 2.5 cents per round

turn (or 1 ª cents per trade side).


Clearing Members who clear Member Firm trades should adjust their billing

systems accordingly.


Clearing Members clearing floor members, accounts should not adjust their

billing systems for such individual members.  NYMEX issues payments directly

to individual members based upon their trading activity.


Floor members who execute Type 3 trades are asked to pay special attention to

NYMEX Rule 6.18 (B) (ii), requiring the executing member to report the alpha

code (badge symbol) of the receiving member on PTS.


Should you have any questions regarding this matter, please feel free to

contact M. Dawn Lowe or Donna Talamo at (212) 299-2370.


